# A–Z Program Manager Workflow

 A — Assess the Need
Clarify the business problem, requestor, urgency, impact, and risk of doing nothing.

B — Build the Business Case
Define expected value, cost, operational impact, resources, and strategic alignment.

C — Confirm Sponsorship
Identify the executive sponsor, business owner, decision maker, and escalation path.

D — Define Scope
Document what is in scope, out of scope, assumed, constrained, and dependent on other teams.

E — Establish Governance
Set meeting cadence, reporting cadence, approval process, decision rights, and steering structure.

F — Form the Team
Identify workstream leads, subject matter experts, support partners, and vendors.

G — Generate the Plan
Build milestones, owners, deliverables, due dates, dependencies, and workback schedules.

 H — Hold Kickoff
Review the purpose, scope, timeline, roles, risks, communication plan, and immediate next steps.

 I — Identify Risks
Log operational, financial, compliance, resource, timeline, stakeholder, and adoption risks.

 J — Join Workstreams
Connect teams, remove silos, clarify handoffs, and build shared visibility.

K — Keep Status Visible
Maintain a project plan, RAID log, action tracker, decision log, and weekly status report.

L — Lead Meetings
Use agendas, capture decisions, assign action items, track blockers, and follow up quickly.

M — Monitor Metrics
Track timeline, budget, quality, adoption, satisfaction, resource load, and risk exposure.

N — Navigate Change
Use change requests, impact assessments, approvals, documentation, and communication.

O — Organize Documentation
Keep charters, plans, notes, approvals, trackers, and final deliverables in one shared location.

P — Prepare Communications
Write clear updates for sponsors, teams, stakeholders, vendors, and impacted users.

Q — Quality Check Deliverables
Review deliverables for accuracy, completeness, readiness, compliance, and acceptance.

R — Resolve Issues
Assign owners, define due dates, escalate blockers, and communicate resolution status.

S — Support Adoption
Create training, FAQs, office hours, feedback loops, and adoption metrics.

T — Track Budget and Resources
Monitor cost centers, invoices, purchase requests, staffing needs, and vendor spend.

U — Update Leadership
Provide progress, risks, decisions needed, budget impact, timeline impact, and next steps.

V — Validate Outcomes
Compare final results against success metrics and confirm stakeholder acceptance.

W — Wrap Up
Close action items, transition ownership, archive files, and document final status.

X — Examine Lessons Learned
Capture what worked, what failed, what should change, and what should be repeated.

Y — Yield Repeatable Processes
Convert successful workflows into SOPs, templates, and playbooks.

Z — Zero In on Continuous Improvement
Update the repository, refine tools, and prepare for the next program.
